cs.AR, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality): The paper mentions mobile systems and user interactions, which could be related to augmented reality applications.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper presents a novel approach for performing energy optimization for interactive mobile web browsing, which could be considered a software engineering problem.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a system (mobile web browsing) by controlling the processor settings, which could be related to systems and control.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper heavily relies on machine learning models to estimate frames per second and optimize energy consumption, which makes this category very likely.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper integrates the proposed techniques to the open-source Chromium browser, which could be related to programming languages.
